\begin_inset Formula $n^2 + 7n + 1$
\end_inset

 is odd.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Proof by cases:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Case 1(n is odd):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

For n odd, it can be shown that 
\begin_inset Formula $n^2 + 7n + 1$
\end_inset

 is of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd + 1$
\end_inset

 which is 
\begin_inset Formula $odd$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Proof by contradiction (
\begin_inset Formula $n^2$
\end_inset

 is odd, for odd n):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Assume 
\begin_inset Formula $n^2 $
\end_inset

 is even, for odd n, then 
\begin_inset Formula $n^2 $
\end_inset

 is divisible by only one even number, 2. It follows that if 
\begin_inset Formula $n^2$
\end_inset

 is divisible by 2, then 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 must be divisible by 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{2}$
\end_inset

, a contradiction since 
\begin_inset Formula $n \in \mathbb{N}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Direct proof(
\begin_inset Formula $7n$
\end_inset

 is odd):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

For any choice of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $7n$
\end_inset

, is not divisible by 2. Therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $7n$
\end_inset

 is odd.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Direct proof (
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd = even$
\end_inset

):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

For some numbers 
\begin_inset Formula $a, b \in \mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $(2a + 1) + (2b +1)$
\end_inset

 is of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray}
(2a+1) + (2b+1) \\
= 2(a+b+1)  \\
= 2n, \: n \in \mathbb{N} \\
\end{eqnarray}
\end_inset

and, by definition, 2n is even.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

Following directly from above, if 
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd = even$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd + 1 = even + 1$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd + 1 = odd$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

It was shown above that 
\begin_inset Formula $n^2 + 7n + 1$
\end_inset

 is of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $odd + odd + 1$
\end_inset

, proving the theorem for 
\begin_inset Formula $n \: odd$
\end_inset

